igt, wie vielfältig und unverzichtbar Transitional Work rund um den Strafvollzug ist.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aThis eBook is made available Open Access under a CC BY-SA 4.0 license: uhttps://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-sa/4.0  aIn German.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Apr 2024) 4aBiopolitik. 4aDeradikalisierung. 4aExtremismus. 4aExtremismusprävention. 4aFundamentalismus. 4aGefängnis. 4aGesellschaftsmitglied. 4aGewalt. 4aJustiz. 4aKategorisierungsarbeit. 4aPolitische Soziologie. 4aPrävention. 4aRecht. 4aRechtssoziologie. 4aSoziologie. 4aTransitional Work. 4aWissenssoziologie. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Sociology / General.2bisacsh  aBiopolitics.  aDeradicalization.  aExtremism.  aFundamentalism.  aJusttice.  aLaw.  aPolitical Sociology.  aPrevention.  aPrison.  aSociology of Knowledge.  aSociology of Law.  aSociology.  aViolence.1 aBruhn, Henrike, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aNegnal, Dörte, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSauerwein, Anna Kristina, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut1 aSauerwein, Anna, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aThiele, Robert, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut1 aThiele, Robert, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb40uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9783839472859zOpen Access7040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783839472859zOpen Access70423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9783839472859/original  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-GOA